OOP Plan:

Actor (Base Class): Handles basic contestant stuff.
    Attributes: name, score
    Methods: add_score(), deduct_score(), get_wager()
    HumanPlayer (Inherits from Actor):
    Methods: choose_action() (waits for your mouse click/keyboard).
    AIPlayer (Inherits from Actor):
    Attributes: accuracy_rate (difficulty level).
    Methods: choose_action() (uses a timer to fake "thinking" time, then randomly picks a correct/incorrect answer based on their accuracy rate).
Question (Clue):
    Attributes: value (e.g., $200), clue_text, choices (list of 3 options), correct_answer, is_daily_double (boolean), is_answered (boolean).
    Methods: check_answer(), reveal().
Board:
    Attributes: categories (a dictionary or list mapping category names to a list of Question objects).
    Methods: draw_board(), select_question(), is_empty().
Game: The main controller.
    Attributes: players (list of Actor objects), current_round (Jeopardy, Double, Final), board, llm_client.
    Methods: start_game(), next_round(), check_game_over().
LLMHelper:
    Methods: generate_questions() (Calls Azure ChatGPT to fetch categories and questions in JSON format).
PowerUp (Base Class) - Bonus Feature:
    Methods: apply_effect()
    ExtraTime, Strike (Subclasses with polymorphic apply_effect() methods).

